Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine buff. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Agelo(chos). From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0035.23 and British Museum 1925,0119.329 and 330 and 2011,5003.255 and 273.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0384)
